%I A395149 #20 Apr 27 2026 00:28:42
%S A395149 1,1,1,1,5,1,1,20,20,1,1,76,275,76,1,1,286,3431,3431,286,1,1,1078,
%T A395149 42238,131714,42238,1078,1,1,4081,527136,4893890,4893890,527136,4081,
%U A395149 1,1,15521,6715171,185250188,527873698,185250188,6715171,15521,1
%N A395149 Triangle of coefficients of characteristic polynomial of negative Pascal matrix with (i+1,j+1)-th entry -C(i+j+2,j).
%C A395149 Row sums are A005130(n+1). See Theorems 32 and 34 in Krattenthaler reference.
%C A395149 Conjecture: The alternating row sum of index 2n is A266091(n)^4 / 3^(2*n) / (2*n+1). For example, 1 - 76 + 275 - 76 + 1 = 15^4 / 3^4 / 5.
%H A395149 Christian Krattenthaler, <a href="https://www.mat.univie.ac.at/~slc/wpapers/s42kratt.html">Advanced Determinant Calculus</a>, Sém. Loth. Comb. 42.
%e A395149 The first few rows are
%e A395149   1;
%e A395149   1, 1;
%e A395149   1, 5, 1;
%e A395149   1, 20, 20, 1;
%e A395149   1, 76, 275, 76, 1;
%e A395149   1, 286, 3431, 3431, 286, 1;
%e A395149   ...
%o A395149 (SageMath)
%o A395149 def m(d):
%o A395149     return matrix(d, d, lambda i, j: -binomial(i + j + 2, j))
%o A395149 [list(m(d).charpoly()) for d in range(12)]
%Y A395149 Similar to A045912 and A395150.
%K A395149 nonn,tabl,new
%O A395149 0,5
%A A395149 _F. Chapoton_, Apr 14 2026
